Snake, Rattle and Roll - Venomous Snakes of Harris County
Texas has over 100 species and subspecies of snakes, but most are not
venomous. Nancy Leary with the Harris County Parks Department Precinct 4 will
teach us how to properly identify the venomous snakes of Harris County how to
avoid getting bitten by a snake and what to do if you are bitten which
harmless snakes are commonly confused with their venomous look-alikes which
snake rolls over and plays dead why it is not in our best interests to kill
snakes.
When:  Friday, March 23 11:30 AM - 12:30 PM
Where: Antioch Park

